  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribute to the Improvement of Victim&#x2019;s Assistance and Knowledge Management in Justice Processes&#x2019; Administration through Capacity-Building and Technical Assistance to the Special Jurisdiction for Peace (JEP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to the improvement of victim assistance and knowledge management for the administration of justice processes, through the strengthening of the Executive Secretariat of the Special Jurisdiction for Peace (JEP), through capacity development and technical assistance, in the updating of tools, information systems and methodologies. The project will develop activities  to increase JEP capacities to carry out justice administration processes, to strengthen monitoring processes through electronic surveillance systems to appearing and to strengthen guidelines, protocols, methodologies and tools to promote the participation and incidence of victims before the JEP.</narrative>
  </description>
